    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-18T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="1219"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1219">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1255a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-18T13:00:00-05:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>39. Informed by Navy Department that launch of <hi rend="italic">Tennessee</hi>
                    was shot at by Turkish forts at Smyrna, which port was visited at your request.
                    Please advise immediately as to facts and make proper representations to Ottoman
                    Government asking explanation of an act which appears to be unfriendly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
